00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:07,957
which now protects
Bohemia and Moravia.

247
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:17,389
Two men left, two right.

248
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:19,914
The whole street.
Every house.

249
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:37,597
I.D., please.

250
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:21,237
This is your cellar.

251
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:26,079
This passage leads
to a staircase.

252
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:32,118
- What was that?
- A round up I guess.

253
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:37,913
How about coming straight to me
next time? For a private screening?

254
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:40,637
I don't think so.

255
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:44,872
But thank you. For everything.

256
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:16,117
What are you doing?

257
00:24:20,120 --> 00:24:21,917
I did a horrible thing.

258
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:25,877
- I went to the cinema.
- Hanka, you can't do that!

259
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:29,953
You know what time it is?
You're under curfew.

260
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:37,510
- We should get divorced, Emil.
- What are you talking about?

261
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:41,191
I'm dangerous for you now.

262
00:24:42,720 --> 00:24:44,517
Come here...

263
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:49,116
You're not dangerous,
just really silly.

264
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:53,950
Drink up. There's rum in it.

265
00:25:03,600 --> 00:25:05,397
How about Franta?

266
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:08,435
Whas going to happen to him?

267
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:13,793
Hard to say. He got arrested.

268
00:25:17,920 --> 00:25:19,717
I don't know...

269
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:24,836
I hope it won't look
as if you exploited this.

270
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:40,076
If I don't say yes,
they'll fire me. If I do...

271
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:49,311
This can't last forever.
We have to hold on.

272
00:25:52,800 --> 00:25:57,555
All right. But make sure
that you stand by me.

273
00:25:57,960 --> 00:26:01,953
That you don't do anything
you shouldn't. Promise?

274
00:26:03,240 --> 00:26:05,037
Don't worry.

275
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:13,315
I'll look after us.
I'll protect you.

276
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:24,677
Hallo, hallo. After a short break
yourfavorite reporter Emil Vrbata,

277
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:29,470
signs on from the German
art exhibit Greatness And Beauty.

278
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:35,519
I am standing in the middle
of this historical hall

279
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:39,070
and right behind me
there is a statue of a rider

280
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:43,358
who is waving his right hand
at an imaginary audience.

281
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:48,317
Now, let me welcome
our special guest,

282
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:51,153
the exhibition's curator,
associate professor Kouba.

283
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:54,550
Could you tell us how this
event came into existence?

284
00:26:54,640 --> 00:27:01,159
The art of the new Germany
is an example for all of us.

285
00:27:01,520 --> 00:27:06,230
Such an exhibit works best
when seen with one's own eyes.

286
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:09,280
How did you manage
this exhibition?

287
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:14,912
It was hard to imagine these
big pieces being moved in here.

288
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:21,516
Fortunately, everything went
smooth thanks to our ability.

289
00:27:22,840 --> 00:27:24,910
We are all happy to hear that.

290
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:28,959
Our Czech workers
have received much praise.

291
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:36,193
- They worked like ants, they...
- Thank you very much, Mr. Kouba.

292
00:27:36,560 --> 00:27:41,714
And now les move
into another hall.

293
00:27:42,240 --> 00:27:45,391
For Voices of Our Home,
at the microphone Emil Vrbata.

294
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:47,352
Thank you, Mr. Kouba.

295
00:28:00,520 --> 00:28:02,317
Good day.

296
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:25,830
...of course, very pleasant,
especially for longer journeys.

297
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:29,993
- I like going to the woods.
- I wouldn't say no to that.

298
00:28:30,560 --> 00:28:33,836
Longer pace and more space.

299
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:39,797
One - two - three...

300
00:28:40,080 --> 00:28:42,833
One -two - three...

301
00:28:46,360 --> 00:28:49,238
Stop! You have to arrive sooner!

302
00:28:50,120 --> 00:28:54,193
I've been working on this for
three days and is still wrong!

303
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:56,077
Les go!

304
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:59,312
One, two, ready!

305
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:11,149
- Hello.
- Hello.

306
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:14,317
Are you Emil Vrbata?

307
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:18,433
For Voices of Our Home,
at the microphone Emil Vrbata.

308
00:29:18,520 --> 00:29:20,875
Could you give us an autograph?

309
00:29:21,120 --> 00:29:26,672
I want an autograph too. Would you
give me one, for old times?

310
00:29:26,800 --> 00:29:29,439
Don't mind me,
I'm not here on business.

311
00:29:29,520 --> 00:29:31,988
We just decided to go out
for the evening.

312
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:36,551
Gentlemen, this is the rising star
in our radio firmament,

313
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:38,910
reporter Emil Vrbata.

314
00:29:39,360 --> 00:29:42,079
- Good day.
- Good day.

315
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:44,071
Pleased to meet you.

316
00:29:45,360 --> 00:29:47,920
Voices of Our Home,
Emil Vabata.

317
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:53,797
Vrbata...

318
00:30:24,320 --> 00:30:26,834
Your hat... Don't forget your hat...

319
00:30:27,080 --> 00:30:28,877
Good night.

320
00:31:15,280 --> 00:31:19,114
- What is it you're wearing?
- I thought you'd like it.

321
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:21,839
Yeah. Is marvelous, splendid.

322
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:28,433
What is it? Anything wrong?

323
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:31,277
Nothing.

324
00:31:31,560 --> 00:31:37,430
All night drinking great schnapps,
smoking expensive cigars,

325
00:31:37,920 --> 00:31:40,912
and in the end
I even sang beautifully.

326
00:31:41,640 --> 00:31:43,835
You think I had a better time?

327
00:31:44,480 --> 00:31:48,598
Sitting here all day alone,
waiting for you to come home?

328
00:31:48,680 --> 00:31:52,036
Emil, take me out.

329
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:55,394
I wouldn't be such a nuisance.

330
00:31:55,760 --> 00:31:58,035
Where to? Is night.

331
00:32:06,760 --> 00:32:08,557
Not now, of course.

332
00:32:15,520 --> 00:32:20,230
Not very lively here, is it?
If you don't like it, we can leave.

333
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:23,870
Why? I like it here. Is like
a Jewish Wenceslas Square.

334
00:32:23,960 --> 00:32:28,192
Is hard when you can't go out.
A park's not possible so this is it.

335
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:31,795
Sure, is logical.
A cemetery is a promenade,

336
00:32:31,880 --> 00:32:34,314
an occupation is protection...

337
00:32:35,960 --> 00:32:40,033
Why don't we go to that café
of ours? We could go there.

338
00:32:42,360 --> 00:32:44,555
Or the gentleman thinks
Jewish cafés stink?

339
00:32:44,640 --> 00:32:48,349
The gentleman doesn't think so,
but he'd rather be here.

340
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:50,237
Is quite pretty here.

341
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:55,117
You're ashamed of me.

342
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:03,677
No, I'm not. Is just that
I don't think is very smart.

343
00:33:04,080 --> 00:33:07,152
That café is really crowded.
Is much better here.

344
00:33:10,920 --> 00:33:15,516
Right now we are in a cozy room,
sensibly furnished.

345
00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:19,548
Opposite me is the cute face
of our young listener

346
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:21,392
trembling with anticipation

347
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:25,314
because she can't wait to hear
some national news.

348
00:33:25,400 --> 00:33:30,155
This is what our youngsters are
like now. Eagerfor new knowledge

349
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:33,516
which our radio station
can bring them.

350
00:33:33,600 --> 00:33:37,878
For Voices of Our Home,
at the microphone, Emil Vrbata.

351
00:33:37,960 --> 00:33:42,511
See? I'm no star but my voice,
thas a different story.

352
00:33:42,880 --> 00:33:47,670
- It will go far.
- Don't joke. You're popular.

353
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:52,357
Half and half. Nothing
compared to actors or sportsmen.

354
00:33:52,560 --> 00:33:54,551
Still, it must affect you.

355
00:33:55,160 --> 00:33:59,711
How about your personal life?
You're married, aren't you?

356
00:34:00,960 --> 00:34:02,757
It doesn't matter...

357
00:34:04,640 --> 00:34:07,359
How did you get
to where you are now?

358
00:34:07,520 --> 00:34:13,914
- What did you do 10 years ago?
- I wanted to be a champion rower.

359
00:34:15,440 --> 00:34:18,113
- Why aren't you, then?
- Because I realized

360
00:34:18,200 --> 00:34:21,556
an average rower
cannot become a champion.

361
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:24,595
But don't quote that either.

362
00:34:26,880 --> 00:34:29,440
You know, is hard work with you.

363
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:33,636
Can you at least
pick a photo for the cover?

364
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:38,277
How about this one?

365
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:42,551
Sorry! I didn't know
you had a visitor.

366
00:34:42,800 --> 00:34:45,758
- She's a journalist.
- I'm just on my way.

367
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:48,115
Is starting any minute now.

368
00:34:57,560 --> 00:35:01,758
4 legs and 4 feet, and winch
and grinch and ring-o-ding

369
00:35:02,120 --> 00:35:05,396
run to the barn
and sleep there til spring.

370
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:10,912
Did you do anything bad this year?

371
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:13,992
- I didn't, Your Saintliness.
- Good, good.

372
00:35:14,080 --> 00:35:15,877
Here you are.

373
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:23,513
What about you in the back?
Did you do anything bad?

374
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:27,797
- Even something little?
- No, I didn't.

375
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:31,557
Here you are.

376
00:35:31,960 --> 00:35:34,110
We'll drink to that.

377
00:35:45,600 --> 00:35:47,158
And now you!

378
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:52,394
Have you been good?
All year? You weren't bad? Really?

379
00:35:53,400 --> 00:35:56,198
Franta! Is it you?

380
00:35:58,560 --> 00:36:00,551
I heard they released you.

381
00:36:01,040 --> 00:36:03,838
- So they have.
- Thas great.

382
00:36:06,320 --> 00:36:08,117
What are you doing here?

383
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:10,437
I work in the archive.

384
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:13,837
Thas good.

385
00:36:16,560 --> 00:36:18,357
Was it bad?

386
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:22,229
Pleasant it wasn't.

387
00:36:27,120 --> 00:36:29,395
You must be angry with me, huh?

388
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:32,672
But there was
nothing else I could do.

389
00:36:32,920 --> 00:36:38,153
Franta, the whole situation,
it was unbearable...

390
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:42,228
I'm not angry with you.
I hope you're a decent man.

391
00:36:42,720 --> 00:36:45,439
- We have to make use of it.
- Of what?

392
00:36:45,520 --> 00:36:48,796
Of your position.
No one will suspect you.

393
00:36:49,440 --> 00:36:53,558
Franta, you're on your own. I'm
in a totally different situation.

394
00:36:53,640 --> 00:36:55,437
Wait!

395
00:36:55,640 --> 00:36:58,916
Sorry, but provocateurs
are everywhere.

396
00:37:00,560 --> 00:37:05,839
Don't worry. Nothing will happen
to anybody. Les spice things up!

397
00:37:06,320 --> 00:37:08,117
Vrbata!

398
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:10,750
You're still a sportsman.

399
00:37:14,760 --> 00:37:17,911
Les show them...
show them that we're men.

400
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:33,996
If you don't give, you get.

401
00:37:42,600 --> 00:37:44,830
Bravo! Bravo!

402
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:04,879
- Sorry. I didn't mean to.
- Is alright. He's used to it.

403
00:38:05,880 --> 00:38:09,077
Won't he take it personally?

404
00:38:12,360 --> 00:38:15,989
You mean when he discovers
you hit him for real?

405
00:38:16,800 --> 00:38:20,793
Don't worry, he's asleep.
But I don't want to sleep.

406
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:30,797
Hi.

407
00:39:36,400 --> 00:39:38,516
Does it have to be so loud?

408
00:39:51,360 --> 00:39:54,909
Look what I've brought you.
A Christmas tree.

409
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:59,949
You're so sweet.
Us Jews are so into Christmas.

410
00:40:00,480 --> 00:40:04,917
- What is it? Are you upset?
- No... I'm not upset.

411
00:40:08,160 --> 00:40:10,515
You'd better go wash yourself.

412
00:40:15,160 --> 00:40:19,073
Someone must have rubbed
herself against my face.

413
00:40:19,440 --> 00:40:23,638
Somehow it all lasted
till morning. We were boxing...

414
00:40:23,800 --> 00:40:25,711
At least don't lie, Emil.

415
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:33,630
- Where are you off to?
- I don't know. I have to go out.

416
00:40:34,960 --> 00:40:37,190
I can't listen to this anymore.

417
00:40:37,280 --> 00:40:42,070
But I'm not lying. Really.
I couldn't leave an official party.

418
00:40:42,360 --> 00:40:44,430
I'm not doing it for myself.

419
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:49,673
Who are you doing it for?
This is not about me anymore.

420
00:40:50,440 --> 00:40:53,238
It was naïve to think
we'd get through this easily.

421
00:40:53,320 --> 00:40:55,595
So far nothing's happened to us.

422
00:40:55,680 --> 00:40:59,229
Emil, hush.
For Goïs sake shut up!

423
00:41:01,560 --> 00:41:03,357
You know what?

424
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:08,118
Do whatever you want.
Is not my fault you're Jewish.

425
00:41:13,120 --> 00:41:16,476
- Were you crying?
- Leave me alone, please.

426
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:20,072
I shan't. You could
do something silly.

427
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:24,317
Silly? You think love is silly?

428
00:41:24,440 --> 00:41:28,877
- So you're a photographer?
- No. I work with corpses.

429
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:33,232
Don't worry.
You are safe here with me.

430
00:41:33,320 --> 00:41:35,834
You want to scare me?

431
00:41:35,920 --> 00:41:38,798
I neverfinished my medical
studies so I work at pathology.

432
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:43,795
Where did you get this? I thought
it never made it to the cinemas.

433
00:41:44,560 --> 00:41:50,157
- It did. It just wasn't screened.
- Do you realize how dangerous I am?

434
00:41:50,240 --> 00:41:52,800
- You're not dangerous.
- How so?

435
00:41:53,520 --> 00:41:55,351
I'm in a cinema
even though I can't be.

436
00:41:55,440 --> 00:41:59,433
But no one can see you here.
Quite a safe danger.

437
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:07,748
Would you like to try
something really dangerous?

438
00:42:07,840 --> 00:42:11,196
Oh how the world
would suddenly seem

439
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:14,710
if I could close my eyes
and dream.

440
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:20,348
Strings of wind
will gently play

441
00:42:20,760 --> 00:42:24,355
All the clouds will cast away

442
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:28,112
Thas just the way
my world should be

443
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:32,435
With my eyes closed
I clearly see

444
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:35,239
- Will you have something?
- Cognac.

445
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:39,635
What are you doing here, Hana?

446
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:46,269
Here goes my wish
when the world goes sore

447
00:42:46,400 --> 00:42:50,075
To close my eyes forever more.

448
00:42:54,040 --> 00:42:57,669
Tell me what would you do
if you were in my place?

449
00:43:01,320 --> 00:43:05,677
You don't lead a bad life.
Your husband takes care of you.

450
00:43:09,960 --> 00:43:11,757
So how did it go?

451
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:14,597
Good.

452
00:43:15,000 --> 00:43:19,198
- What did you tell him?
- Nothing. It wasn't about him.

453
00:43:21,760 --> 00:43:23,830
Do you still have some film?

454
00:43:31,720 --> 00:43:33,790
Jews Not Admitted

455
00:43:33,880 --> 00:43:37,031
Box Office
Jews Forbidden To Enter

456
00:43:41,800 --> 00:43:43,791
Pure Aryan Business

457
00:44:05,680 --> 00:44:07,955
- Hi there, sailors.
- Hello.

458
00:44:17,760 --> 00:44:22,959
Admit it. You're old. You can never
keep up with these young stallions.

459
00:44:23,040 --> 00:44:27,079
I could care less.
I'm worried about other things.

460
00:44:27,160 --> 00:44:29,833
I see. You know what?

461
00:44:30,880 --> 00:44:34,873
I've been thinking and I say
screw your conscience.

462
00:44:35,000 --> 00:44:36,877
Your wife should be grateful

463
00:44:36,960 --> 00:44:40,714
you make such sacrifices. There's
nothing she can reproach you with.

464
00:44:40,800 --> 00:44:45,078
She doesn't reproach me.
She simply doesn't talk to me.

465
00:44:47,280 --> 00:44:49,475
Can't you make a deal with her?

466
00:44:49,800 --> 00:44:53,429
How can I make a deal with her
when we don't talk?

467
00:44:53,880 --> 00:44:56,713
Or do you consult
these things with Tomek?

468
00:44:56,880 --> 00:44:59,917
No. Thas what I've got you for.

469
00:45:05,720 --> 00:45:09,076
- Why don't we consult more often?
- Because we can't.

470
00:45:09,160 --> 00:45:13,073
- You know I'm getting married.
- I know but I don't get it.

471
00:45:13,160 --> 00:45:15,071
You know is good with us.

472
00:45:15,160 --> 00:45:20,075
Emil, I thought a sportsman can
tell when is only about sport.

473
00:45:26,400 --> 00:45:29,198
What if we take them
with us tonight?

474
00:45:47,960 --> 00:45:49,757
23...

475
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:51,797
24...

476
00:45:52,480 --> 00:45:54,277
25...

477
00:45:55,040 --> 00:45:56,837
26...

478
00:45:57,600 --> 00:46:00,273
- 27!
- Bravo!

479
00:46:02,240 --> 00:46:03,878
You can't do this!

480
00:46:03,960 --> 00:46:07,555
Ladies and gentlemen, this here
is our caretaker, in person.

481
00:46:07,640 --> 00:46:10,996
And this is his guest book
so les all sign it now.

482
00:46:11,080 --> 00:46:14,277
This party was
duly announced and permitted.

483
00:46:14,360 --> 00:46:17,591
Don't worry. You're safe with me.

484
00:46:22,920 --> 00:46:25,388
Wait. I haven't signed yet.

485
00:46:43,040 --> 00:46:47,033
The one with the gate
doesn't count. I didn't get in.

486
00:46:47,560 --> 00:46:52,350
It counts. What would he have done
if he'd known you're Jewish?

487
00:47:06,000 --> 00:47:10,357
What are you staring at?
Haven't you seen The Springman?

488
00:47:11,480 --> 00:47:14,040
You haven't because
no one's ever seen him.

489
00:47:14,120 --> 00:47:18,477
He's a mysterious phantom
who always escapes the Nazis.

