740
01:16:04,920 --> 01:16:08,276
Things have changed.
I can't tell you more.

741
01:16:20,720 --> 01:16:22,517
You'll come back.

742
01:17:02,160 --> 01:17:05,516
- Hey.
- Hi. Why is it so dark here?

743
01:17:06,320 --> 01:17:08,117
Is safer.

744
01:17:09,400 --> 01:17:11,197
Whave you got?

745
01:17:24,880 --> 01:17:27,314
You really think this will help?

746
01:17:28,880 --> 01:17:31,872
Is a cover.
Thas the way they do it.

747
01:17:50,480 --> 01:17:54,314
Emil, you don't believe in me.
You think I don't get it.

748
01:17:54,400 --> 01:17:58,473
- What don't you understand?
- I'm not totally blind.

749
01:17:58,600 --> 01:18:03,799
If you'd just give me a hint, I'd
understand you're up to something.

750
01:18:04,320 --> 01:18:08,677
And I'll keep quiet, promise.
But how about the bicycle?

751
01:18:10,160 --> 01:18:12,435
People keep talking about it.

752
01:18:12,920 --> 01:18:17,630
But they've already got it.
Is on display in the Bata store.

753
01:18:18,080 --> 01:18:19,877
I mean the other one.

754
01:18:20,720 --> 01:18:23,917
This is the bicycle
they're looking for.

755
01:18:25,640 --> 01:18:29,428
Emil, you don't have
to patronize me. I'll help you.

756
01:18:29,520 --> 01:18:33,798
No way! You'll be better off
if you don't know anything.

757
01:18:34,080 --> 01:18:36,992
I'll sort it out.
I'll take care of it.

758
01:18:43,040 --> 01:18:47,477
This morning Reich Protector
Reinhard Heydrich,

759
01:18:47,560 --> 01:18:55,752
succumbed to injuries
suffered during the deadly attack.

760
01:18:56,440 --> 01:19:01,275
On the occasion of the transport
of the Deputy Protector's remains,

761
01:19:01,360 --> 01:19:04,989
before the coverage
of the funeral itself,

762
01:19:05,240 --> 01:19:10,234
we will broadcast a radio workers'
oath of loyalty to the German Reich.

763
01:19:10,320 --> 01:19:13,835
If anyone misses this
without a serious reason,

764
01:19:13,920 --> 01:19:17,913
there will be consequences.
Thas all. You can go.

765
01:19:27,760 --> 01:19:29,557
Vrbata.

766
01:19:31,720 --> 01:19:34,314
Though I withdrew you
from the microphone,

767
01:19:34,400 --> 01:19:37,676
our management wants you
to read the oath.

768
01:19:37,760 --> 01:19:41,958
They think it should be read
aloud by a popular person.

769
01:19:43,760 --> 01:19:45,557
This time, be punctual.

770
01:19:46,040 --> 01:19:51,478
Any lapse can be regarded
as a nod to the assassination.

771
01:19:57,800 --> 01:20:01,713
Emil? There's someone
waiting for you at the gate.

772
01:20:01,880 --> 01:20:04,235
- What do they want?
- Nothing.

773
01:20:05,800 --> 01:20:10,078
Listen, I hear
if they don't catch anyone,

774
01:20:10,200 --> 01:20:14,113
they'll execute every
tenth Czech. Can it be true?

775
01:20:16,120 --> 01:20:17,917
Why are you asking me?

776
01:20:18,200 --> 01:20:21,351
I know nothing about it
and don't want to talk about it!

777
01:20:21,440 --> 01:20:23,237
You know about Franta?

778
01:20:24,120 --> 01:20:25,917
He was executed.

779
01:20:43,720 --> 01:20:47,076
Why didn't you call?
I thought you were ill.

780
01:20:47,520 --> 01:20:50,193
- Were you ill?
- What are you doing here?

781
01:20:50,280 --> 01:20:52,555
I've brought you your bow tie.

782
01:20:53,120 --> 01:20:56,669
And I also came to tell you
I probably love you.

783
01:20:58,280 --> 01:21:02,273
Krista, thas great
but this is not the right time.

784
01:21:03,720 --> 01:21:07,030
- You're not happy?
- Don't you understand the situation?

785
01:21:07,120 --> 01:21:09,998
- What situation?
- I can't talk about it now.

786
01:21:10,080 --> 01:21:11,718
Is dangerous...

787
01:21:11,800 --> 01:21:15,918
We've been looking for you upstairs
the whole time, and here you are.

788
01:21:16,640 --> 01:21:18,710
You have a pretty daughter.

789
01:21:19,640 --> 01:21:21,631
I don't have any daughter.

790
01:21:23,400 --> 01:21:25,197
We know you don't.

791
01:21:27,480 --> 01:21:29,277
Les go.

792
01:21:30,640 --> 01:21:34,792
...Miks Frantisek, Police Sergeant,

793
01:21:35,240 --> 01:21:41,031
born 12 March 1915, living in Tabor.

794
01:21:42,720 --> 01:21:47,748
Convicted of conspiring
and abetting the perpetrators

795
01:21:47,840 --> 01:21:52,789
in the assassination
of SS Obergruppenführer Heydrich.

796
01:21:53,040 --> 01:21:57,238
I still see him, how he looked
at me, how they led him out.

797
01:21:58,960 --> 01:22:03,158
Definitely he wanted to go to you
and tell you the truth about us.

798
01:22:08,800 --> 01:22:12,998
- Only he didn't make it.
- When exactly was it? - What?

799
01:22:13,760 --> 01:22:17,116
- What time did they grab him?
- I don't know.

800
01:22:18,800 --> 01:22:21,030
Around noon.

801
01:22:31,880 --> 01:22:33,677
You've got to help me.

802
01:22:36,520 --> 01:22:38,317
Can you keep a secret?

803
01:22:49,480 --> 01:22:52,916
Why are you keeping
a bicycle in an airshaft?

804
01:22:53,680 --> 01:22:54,999
You have to get it out of here.

805
01:22:55,080 --> 01:22:56,877
Good day, Mr. Vrbata.

806
01:22:57,640 --> 01:22:59,437
Good day.

807
01:23:02,000 --> 01:23:04,195
Do you know
why we've called you here?

808
01:23:04,280 --> 01:23:07,750
If they don't find anything
they can't charge him.

809
01:23:07,840 --> 01:23:11,515
Shall I call home...
that I'm not coming?

810
01:23:11,840 --> 01:23:16,152
Why wouldn't you go home?
Have you done something?

811
01:23:19,680 --> 01:23:23,912
Wait a minute. We're needlessly
afraid. This is our bicycle.

812
01:23:24,000 --> 01:23:25,911
What do you mean, your bicycle?

813
01:23:26,000 --> 01:23:29,675
What are you babbling about? This
is the bicycle they're looking for!

814
01:23:29,760 --> 01:23:31,955
Do you know this photograph?

815
01:23:33,280 --> 01:23:37,956
This bicycle is from our house. Emil
took it as he was rushing to work.

816
01:23:38,040 --> 01:23:41,749
What do you mean?
Emil has never taken anything.

817
01:23:41,840 --> 01:23:46,470
He did. He overslept at my place.
So then he just borrowed the bike

818
01:23:46,560 --> 01:23:49,870
and as he was in such a rush
he forgot to bring it back.

819
01:23:49,960 --> 01:23:52,758
He probably
didn't want to tell you.

820
01:23:54,080 --> 01:23:56,992
- What?
- You have to get divorced.

821
01:23:57,080 --> 01:23:59,355
You see, we love each other...

822
01:24:04,160 --> 01:24:07,630
You can't take them seriously.
Maybe they look like adults

823
01:24:07,720 --> 01:24:10,154
but really they're still boys.

824
01:24:10,800 --> 01:24:15,669
They don't do anything. Only
exercise. Nothing more than that.

825
01:24:17,080 --> 01:24:21,312
No one's banned exercising yet.
Is just games.

826
01:24:37,840 --> 01:24:39,637
Turn around.

827
01:24:45,040 --> 01:24:48,794
And? Do they strike you
as if they're playing games?

828
01:24:50,720 --> 01:24:53,188
Okay, gentlemen, les go.

829
01:24:53,720 --> 01:24:55,517
Move it.

830
01:24:55,960 --> 01:24:58,394
Don't you want to tell me something?

831
01:24:58,520 --> 01:25:00,317
I don't know.

832
01:25:00,440 --> 01:25:03,716
I don't know. I haven't
seen them for ages.

833
01:25:04,760 --> 01:25:08,753
And you won't ever see them again.
The paradox is that they think

834
01:25:08,840 --> 01:25:11,149
you informed against them.

835
01:25:12,160 --> 01:25:14,469
But I haven't informed
against anyone.

836
01:25:14,560 --> 01:25:16,357
Thas not essential.

837
01:25:18,320 --> 01:25:22,108
Ultimately, it really
doesn't matter who did it.

838
01:25:22,520 --> 01:25:26,035
You simply have to decide
on which side you stand.

839
01:25:27,200 --> 01:25:29,998
You have the night
to think about it.

840
01:25:48,600 --> 01:25:51,433
Petr. Turn it off!

841
01:25:52,440 --> 01:25:56,149
Is a national day of mourning.
Someone might report you!

842
01:25:57,680 --> 01:26:00,399
Safety with you
is farfrom safe...

843
01:26:01,200 --> 01:26:04,875
I close my eyes
and feel so grand...

844
01:26:17,640 --> 01:26:19,437
Come on. We have to go!

845
01:26:19,920 --> 01:26:22,309
Police here! Open up!

846
01:26:25,600 --> 01:26:28,512
Showing a film is forbidden!

847
01:26:29,000 --> 01:26:30,911
Stop the film immediately!

848
01:26:31,200 --> 01:26:32,997
Run.

849
01:26:33,600 --> 01:26:35,830
I'll take care of this. Run!

850
01:26:35,920 --> 01:26:38,593
Force the door!

851
01:26:48,320 --> 01:26:51,995
- Is a national day of mourning!
- You support the assassination!

852
01:26:52,080 --> 01:26:54,196
You're under arrest!

853
01:27:34,880 --> 01:27:36,677
- Hello?
- Hello?

854
01:27:36,800 --> 01:27:38,597
Hanka?

855
01:27:40,480 --> 01:27:44,519
- Is me. Where are you?
- Is it you, Krista?

856
01:27:44,600 --> 01:27:48,593
I thought I'd never see you
again. I'll come for you.

857
01:27:50,720 --> 01:27:57,068
We radio workers swear to
stay unfalteringly loyal

858
01:27:57,240 --> 01:27:59,674
to president Hacha

859
01:28:01,320 --> 01:28:03,993
and our lawful government

860
01:28:05,480 --> 01:28:11,191
and assure them
we want to be fully duteous

861
01:28:11,680 --> 01:28:17,869
and that we shall
fulfill our duties to the Reich

862
01:28:18,360 --> 01:28:22,035
with the highest faithfulness
and honesty,

863
01:28:22,160 --> 01:28:26,756
being aware that theirfight for a
better order in Europe is also ours.

864
01:28:26,840 --> 01:28:31,038
We fully agree with Mr. Benes
being called a public enemy

865
01:28:31,120 --> 01:28:32,917
of the Czech nation.

866
01:28:33,080 --> 01:28:36,595
If it were not for instigations
by Mr. Benes, his people abroad,

867
01:28:36,680 --> 01:28:40,195
our country would be
the most blessed and quiet place

868
01:28:40,280 --> 01:28:43,875
- in an otherwise disorderly Europe.
- The sun is setting.

869
01:28:43,960 --> 01:28:47,430
Lights of fire, a scent of flowers.

870
01:28:49,720 --> 01:28:54,635
It was a hard,
mournful and sad day.

871
01:28:57,080 --> 01:29:04,350
At 7pm, when long shadows
are cast over the Castle courtyard,

872
01:29:04,920 --> 01:29:09,596
Deputy Protector,
SS Obergruppenführer

873
01:29:10,000 --> 01:29:15,632
Reinhard Heydrich shall leave
the Prague Castle forever.

874
01:30:47,840 --> 01:30:49,637
Where is Vrbata?

875
01:30:50,840 --> 01:30:52,637
Third floor.

